HEADWORD: Unchurch
<hw>Un*church"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>church</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To expel, or
cause to separate, from a church; to excommunicate.</def> <rj><au>Sir M.
Hale.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To deprive of the character, privileges, and
authority of a church.</def> <rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uncia</ent>⟦br⟧
